{"type":"RECORD","stream":"stream_trello_cards","record":{"id":"649b692b8cdc5aa6082af71c","badges":{"fogbugz":"","checkItems":0,"checkItemsChecked":0,"checkItemsEarliestDue":null,"comments":0,"attachments":0,"description":true,"due":null,"dueComplete":false,"start":null,"location":false,"votes":0,"viewingMemberVoted":false,"subscribed":false},"checkItemStates":[],"closed":false,"dueComplete":false,"dateLastActivity":"2023-06-27T22:56:44.289Z","desc":"##Add labels by clicking the \"Labels\" button on the right -->##\n\n##What are labels?##\n\nLabels are great ways to differentiate the type of tasks your team has.\n\nFor example: \n\n(yellow) **Copy Request:** Any doc, task, or page that needs a grammatical overview or general words in order for it to be done.\n\n(red) **Priority:** This task needs to be finished first before anything else gets done. Communicate the urgency with this handy label.\n\n(purple) **Design Team:** Use this label to indicate that the design team is involved in some capacity so there's never any confusion.\n\n(green) **Halp:** A hilarious plea? Yes. A useful indication? Definitely. Labels can be used for anything, including an indication that someone needs assistance with a task.\n\n**Bonus**\nNotice the patterns on the labels: designed for those that may not be able to see colors properly. \n ","due":null,"dueReminder":null,"email":null,"idBoard":"649b692b8cdc5aa6082af698","idChecklists":[],"idList":"649b692b8cdc5aa6082af69f","idMembers":[],"idMembersVoted":[],"idShort":19,"idAttachmentCover":null,"labels":[{},{},{},{},{}],"idLabels":["649b692b8cdc5aa6082af739","649b692b8cdc5aa6082af730","649b692b8cdc5aa6082af736","649b692b8cdc5aa6082af73c","649b692b8cdc5aa6082af72d"],"manualCoverAttachment":false,"name":"Trello Tip: Card labels! What do they mean? (Click for more info)","pos":15360,"shortLink":"g4ot9LrI","shortUrl":"https://trello.com/c/g4ot9LrI","start":null,"subscribed":false,"url":"https://trello.com/c/g4ot9LrI/19-trello-tip-card-labels-what-do-they-mean-click-for-more-info","isTemplate":false,"cardRole":null},"time_extracted":"2025-06-10T15:11:03.285625+00:00"}
{"type":"RECORD","stream":"stream_trello_cards","record":{"id":"649b692b8cdc5aa6082af724","badges":{"fogbugz":"","checkItems":0,"checkItemsChecked":0,"checkItemsEarliestDue":null,"comments":0,"attachments":2,"description":true,"due":null,"dueComplete":false,"start":null,"location":false,"votes":0,"viewingMemberVoted":false,"subscribed":false},"checkItemStates":[],"closed":false,"dueComplete":false,"dateLastActivity":"2023-06-27T22:56:44.722Z","desc":"Moving projects across the finish line is rewarding, but it\u2019s far from easy. When you have multiple teams involved on a single project, it\u2019s even tougher. Are you breaking out into a sweat just thinking about it? Here\u2019s the good news: no matter what team you're on, this [project plan template](https://id.atlassian.com/login?login_prompt=none&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlassian.com%2Fsoftware%2Fconfluence%2Ftemplates%2Fproject-plan%3FTrelloTemplate%3D5c3e2fdb0fa92e43b849d838 \"\u200c\") from our friends at Confluence makes it easier to manage projects of any size and complexity, all while keeping stakeholders in the loop along the way.\n\n## :tada: [Try out the template!](https://id.atlassian.com/login?login_prompt=none&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlassian.com%2Fsoftware%2Fconfluence%2Ftemplates%2Fproject-plan%3FTrelloTemplate%3D5c3e2fdb0fa92e43b849d838 \"\u200c\") :tada:","due":null,"dueReminder":null,"email":null,"idBoard":"649b692b8cdc5aa6082af698","idChecklists":[],"idList":"649b692b8cdc5aa6082af69f","idMembers":[],"idMembersVoted":[],"idShort":23,"idAttachmentCover":"649b692c8cdc5aa6082af8c1","labels":[],"idLabels":[],"manualCoverAttachment":false,"name":"Move work forward with a project plan","pos":19968,"shortLink":"DVkE4gUW","shortUrl":"https://trello.com/c/DVkE4gUW","start":null,"subscribed":false,"url":"https://trello.com/c/DVkE4gUW/23-move-work-forward-with-a-project-plan","isTemplate":false,"cardRole":null},"time_extracted":"2025-06-10T15:11:03.285833+00:00"}
{"type":"RECORD","stream":"stream_trello_cards","record":{"id":"649b692b8cdc5aa6082af6f5","badges":{"fogbugz":"","checkItems":6,"checkItemsChecked":0,"checkItemsEarliestDue":null,"comments":0,"attachments":0,"description":true,"due":null,"dueComplete":false,"start":null,"location":false,"votes":0,"viewingMemberVoted":false,"subscribed":false},"checkItemStates":[],"closed":false,"dueComplete":false,"dateLastActivity":"2023-06-27T22:56:43.889Z","desc":"Whoa! Look! It's a checklist\u2014you can create tasks, tag your teammates, and check-off tasks as you go and achieve milestones.","due":null,"dueReminder":null,"email":null,"idBoard":"649b692b8cdc5aa6082af698","idChecklists":["649b692b8cdc5aa6082af6f7"],"idList":"649b692b8cdc5aa6082af69f","idMembers":[],"idMembersVoted":[],"idShort":1,"idAttachmentCover":null,"labels":[],"idLabels":[],"manualCoverAttachment":false,"name":"Project \"Teamwork Dream Work\" Launch Timeline","pos":24576,"shortLink":"hysYk4nC","shortUrl":"https://trello.com/c/hysYk4nC","start":null,"subscribed":false,"url":"https://trello.com/c/hysYk4nC/1-project-teamwork-dream-work-launch-timeline","isTemplate":false,"cardRole":null},"time_extracted":"2025-06-10T15:11:03.285967+00:00"}
{"type":"RECORD","stream":"stream_trello_cards","record":{"id":"649b692b8cdc5aa6082af726","badges":{"fogbugz":"","checkItems":0,"checkItemsChecked":0,"checkItemsEarliestDue":null,"comments":0,"attachments":2,"description":true,"due":null,"dueComplete":false,"start":null,"location":false,"votes":0,"viewingMemberVoted":false,"subscribed":false},"checkItemStates":[],"closed":false,"dueComplete":false,"dateLastActivity":"2023-06-27T22:56:44.846Z","desc":"Love the ease of Trello but looking for more complex project management features? Check out **Jira Work Management**!\n\nJira Work Management combines powerful features _(subtasks, reporting, and more!)_ with an easy-to-use interface. Because it\u2019s brought to you by the same company as Trello, it will also integrate with your Trello board, letting you manage your work wherever feels right to you.\n\n### Curious? Check out this [project management template](https://id.atlassian.com/login?login_prompt=none&continue=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlassian.com%2Fsoftware%2Fjira%2Ftemplates%2Fproject-management%3FTrelloTemplate%3D5c3e2fdb0fa92e43b849d838 \"\u200c\") to get started!","due":null,"dueReminder":null,"email":null,"idBoard":"649b692b8cdc5aa6082af698","idChecklists":[],"idList":"649b692b8cdc5aa6082af69f","idMembers":[],"idMembersVoted":[],"idShort":24,"idAttachmentCover":"649b692c8cdc5aa6082af8cd","labels":[],"idLabels":[],"manualCoverAttachment":true,"name":"Looking for even more project management features?","pos":57344,"shortLink":"mAuIKJQ9","shortUrl":"https://trello.com/c/mAuIKJQ9","start":null,"subscribed":false,"url":"https://trello.com/c/mAuIKJQ9/24-looking-for-even-more-project-management-features","isTemplate":false,"cardRole":null},"time_extracted":"2025-06-10T15:11:03.286092+00:00"}
